</code></pre>
<p>How can I reliably read dates from the database and convert them back into an integer, or at least to a <code>chrono::DateTime</code> struct?</p>
<p>Right now, the function attempting to parse the date string returned in the format above is:</p>
<pre class="lang-rs prettyprint-override"><code>pub fn date_string_to_int(d: &amp;str) -&gt; FlusterResult&lt;i64&gt; {
    let format = &quot;%Y-%m-%dT%T%.f&quot;;
